ame":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":20,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Elizabeth Metham was born about 1362, in Metham, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Sir Thomas Metham III, was 13 and her mother, Elizabeth Stapleton, was 15. She married Sir William Constable in 1385, in Halsham, Yorkshire, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1391, in Yorkshire, England, at the age of 30, and was buried in Halsham, Yorkshire, England."},"et":{"Abt 1362–1391":"umbes 1362–1391","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1358–1419":"1358–1419","1385–Male":"1385–Surnud","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1391":"1391","Abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1348":"1348","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","about 1385":"umbes 1385","1419":"1419","1416":"1416","Halsham, Yorkshire, England":"Halsham, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Metham, Yorkshire, England":"Cottam, Yorkshire East Riding, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1362–1391":"noin 1362–1391","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1358–1419":"1358–1419","1385–Male":"1385–Kuollut","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1391":"1391","Abt 1362":"noin 1362","1348":"1348","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","about 1385":"noin 1385","1419":"1419","1416":"1416","Halsham, Yorkshire, England":"Halsham, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Metham, Yorkshire, England":"Cottam, Yorkshire East Riding, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1362–1391":"environ 1362–1391","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1358–1419":"1358–1419","1385–Male":"1385–Décédé","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1391":"1391","Abt 1362":"environ 1362","1348":"1348","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","about 1385":"environ 1385","1419":"1419","1416":"1416","Halsham, Yorkshire, England":"Halsham, Everwyck, Angleterre","Yorkshire, England":"Everwyck, Angleterre","Metham, Yorkshire, England":"Cottam, Yorkshire East Riding, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Elizabeth Metham est née environ 1362, à Metham, Everwyck, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni, son père, Sir Thomas Metham III, avait 13 ans et sa mère, Elizabeth Stapleton, avait 15 ans. Elle a épousé Sir William Constable en 1385, à Halsham, Everwyck, Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fils. Elle est décédée en 1391, à Everwyck, Angleterre, à l’âge de 30 ans, et a été enterrée à Halsham, Everwyck, Angleterre."},"de":{"Abt 1362–1391":"um 1362–1391","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Verstorben","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1358–1419":"1358–1419","1385–Male":"1385–Verstorben","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1391":"1391","Abt 1362":"um 1362","1348":"1348","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","about 1385":"um 1385","1419":"1419","1416":"1416","Halsham, Yorkshire, England":"Halsham, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Metham, Yorkshire, England":"Cottam, Yorkshire East Riding, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Elizabeth Metham um 1362 in Metham, Yorkshire, England, United Kingdom geboren wurde, war ihr Vater Sir Thomas Metham III 13 und ihre Mutter Elizabeth Stapleton 15. Sie hat 1385 in Halsham, Yorkshire, England Sir William Constable geheiratet. Sie hatten mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie starb 1391 im Alter von 30 Jahren in Yorkshire, England und wurde in Halsham, Yorkshire, England begraben."},"ht":{"Abt 1362–1391":"about 1362–1391","1362–1391":"1362–1391","1370–Male":"1370–Desede","1382–1416":"1382–1416","1358–1419":"1358–1419","1385–Male":"1385–Desede","1351–1403":"1351–1403","1348–1400":"1348–1400","1385":"1385","1362":"1362","1351":"1351","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1391":"1391","Abt 1362":"about 1362","1348":"1348","1403":"1403","1358":"1358","1400":"1400","about 1385":"about 1385","1419":"1419","1416":"1416","Halsham, Yorkshire, England":"Halsham, Yorkshire, England","Yorkshire, England":"Yorkshire, England","Metham, Yorkshire, England":"